[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    343[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAWS Lambda for per-stage glue logic.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m The cohort-construction dispatcher, the propensity-score-invocation orchestrator, the CATE-estimator-ensemble runner, the uncertainty-quantification computer, the calibration-drift detector, the OOD-flag computer, the on-demand-scoring orchestrator, the briefing-generator, the validator, the decision-recorder, and the prediction-to-outcome matcher all run as Lambdas.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    344[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    345[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAmazon API Gateway and Amazon Cognito for the on-demand scoring API.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m The clinician-facing decision-support component is exposed as an authenticated API consumed by the EHR integration layer. API Gateway provides the endpoint, Cognito (or the institution's identity provider via SAML or OIDC) provides authentication, and per-clinician audit logs go to CloudTrail. The EHR integration is typically through a SMART on FHIR app or a CDS Hooks endpoint, both of which the API supports.[K
